TITLE: ne_dxx_discountslp_redirect_0519_av_2
PRIMARY GOAL: Increase exposure to Ticketmonster.
DESCRIPTION: Discounts CAA LP v. AEM LP
LEARNINGS: Throughout the duration of the test, the bounce rate is significantly lower and the number of overall exit link instances is significantly higher for the AEM page versus the CAA page. Lower bounce rate can indicate that the user is engaged with the content on first impression. Higher instances of exit links can indicate the users are able to find discounts that are enticing to them. Creating a page in AEM provides us with the flexibility to highlight key partners and discounts, while also providing an opportunity for future personalization efforts.

PRIMARY GOAL: Increase entry rate into Auto Insurance page by mobile navigation.
DESCRIPTION: Get a Auto Insurance Quote under Insurance
LEARNINGS:
Though this test did not reach the targeted sample size for a 10% lift, no early indicators were observed to continue this test for the entirety of the projected duration.

        The trendline for engagement indicates that Experience B had no significant impact on entry into the Auto Insurance Overview page through the mobile navigation. We can assume that users who intend to search for Auto Insurance are able to navigate to the page. It is possible that additional variables have impacted test validity due to the long test flight. These variables include volume of traffic from campaigns, seasonality, etc.

TITLE: ne_ixx_ixxhp_widget_statezip_0719_av
PRIMARY GOAL: Increase entry rate into Auto Insurance funnels through widget interaction.
DESCRIPTION: State dropdown v. Zip code
LEARNINGS:
We reached the sample size of 16,752 visitors per experience, targeting for a 10.00% lift and observed neither a positive or negative lift in engagement.  
        The trendline for engagement depicts an longer duration of positive impact for Experience B, but without conclusive data when considering a 10.00% lift. We can assume that adding the zip code neither positive or negative to the customer journey to Insurance Products available in the widget drop down. This space requires more iterations and testing to create a measurable impact on engagement rate.

DESCRIPTION: MA Auto v. Mapfre white label
LEARNINGS: Based on page visitation, the MA Auto funnel produced more web leads than Mapfre, when including knock outs, in this time period. We did not receive enough volume to conclusively declare a winner for the web experience, however, as the lift bounds scale between -17% to 0.5% and through observation of the overall trend of this test, we can predict that the MA Auto Application will at least get an equal number of users through the funnel, if not more.

When recalculating for a 12.00% as indicated in today’s analysis, we have reached our targeted sample size of 885 visitors per offer, thus conclusively determining B as a higher performing experience.

TITLE: ne_mxx_myprofile_reinstate_funnel_redesign_0719_av
PRIMARY GOAL: Increase reinstate conversions through My Profile for Plus and Premier targeting all visitors.
DESCRIPTION: Added benefits to coverage cards.
LEARNINGS:
Experience B appeared to have a negative impact on overall reinstate completions, but concluded with a positive lift of 24.8% of reinstate completions that resulted in a plus or premier membership type.  

This may indicate that users who saw Experience B may have abandoned the funnel to seek additional information, but those who intended to reinstate, did so with a plus or premier status. It appears that Basic Reinstate Memberships had the most negative output, with a 35.7% conversion rate in A, and 24.8% conversion rate in B, however, to determine a statistically significant winner for overall transactions will require an additional amount of time.
